JOHANNESBURG - Sports Minister Nathi Mthethwa has exercised his powers in terms of Section 13 of the National Sport and Recreation Act and has stripped Cricket South Africa (CSA) of national recognition. The move strips the cricket body as the authority to run the sport in the country. The move comes after its members' council voted not to implement a new memorandum of incorporation, which would have meant having more independent directors, as well as an independent chair. ANNOUNCEMENT: CSA Interim Board statement on correspondence from Minister Mthethwa.Read more: https://t.co/y25XyUJivK pic.twitter.com/ZY6BO8SFaR  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.